   trade. WCAs are bilateral framework agreements that establish
   comprehensive guidelines on the development, production, and exchange of
   conventional arms. Substantively, WCAs regulate such core areas as
   procurement and contracting, defense-based research and development, and
   defense industrial cooperation. These agreements have proliferated
   dramatically since the mid-1990s. They now number nearly 700, with 30-40
   new WCAs signed each year. Newly collected data are used to analyze the
   effect of WCAs on import and export of conventional weapons. To control
